This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: 20 lines of code #37
Dreamcatcher Forest #565
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Возвышение #32
metadata.description:
Возвышение (Eng.: Elevation) is the next step of my study of Suprematism, textures and colours, partially inspired by Lazar Khidekel works. 
The work depicts the superiority of the simplest geometric forms and colours over everything else.

——————

Rendering takes around 20-30 seconds at 60 fps, might take longer on older devices.
Press [Arrow Up / Down] to increase / decrease drawing speed.
Press [1…6] to change an image resolution up to 10k.
Press [S] after the image is rendered to save it.

Created using p5.js.

metadata.name: Unknown Museum – Genesis #118
metadata.description:
"Unknown Museum" is a conceptual NFT project that mixes illustration and randomness with mystic figures such as demons, angels and nature elements.

The NFT will always be composed of 4 random tiles and 1 random frame. 

These are the available elements:

5 x Angels
5 x Demons
5 x Flowers
5 x Birds
5 x Humans
5 x Stars
5 x Vases
5 x Frames

Each tile has up to 6 different color variations.

Pro tip: Try to come up with a backstory for your nft results based on its characters and share with us ✨

metadata.name: Human Exclusion Zones #10
metadata.description:
Human Exclusion Zones started out as a speculative exploration at the intersection of automated factory floors and biopunk. As we fantasize about the post-human condition a lot of progress has been made in mathematics, physics, chemistry - when do we similarly accelerate in the domain of biology and how might it affect us? Remember the pandemic anyone!

This artwork is generated using grid noise across scales and superimposing them with reaction diffusion to bring in a certain feeling of the organic process in a very dead environment. The ongoing feedback effects keeps the work morphing and changing overtime, as though our smart organic robot friends are evolving and changing overtime. 

Press 's' to export a high-res version in LIVE mode

Made with love using cables.gl 
 
Easter Egg:
Press 'd' to open up settings in the LIVE mode
* You can feed in your own images to use this NFT as a small tool to get stylized versions of your input image(Make sure your images are 1x1)
